headline: Chocolatiers Burned by Cocoa Rally Still Need to Rebuild Hedges
summary: (Bloomberg) -- It looked like cocoa supplies were improving earlier this season after the worst deficit ever, giving chocolatiers paying through the nose for beans an incentive to sit out and wait for lower prices.
